This project is a macOS helper app that allows you to bind any command to any global hotkey. It uses swift 5 and a simple build system (`build.sh`). The UI uses direct Cocoa calls, no XIB.

Since it's currently in development, refactor what is needed, depending on the task. Backwards compatibility is also not an issue whatsoever.

Modern UI stuff could be used since we're targeting macOS 13 or higher. Feel free to do research using one-liners with `swift -e` if needed.

Use `build.sh` to build the project and check for possible compilation errors (it's a wrapper around `swift build` that does everything to make a proper app bundle).

Don't overthink. Ask if something is unclear. If encountered a difficult problem first explain it and ask advice from the user.